[[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba's]] majordomo, the [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] known as [[Bib Fortuna/Legends|Bib Fortuna]], is the main character in "'''Of the Day's Annoyances: Bib Fortuna's Tale'''" by [[M. Shayne Bell]], which appeared in ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'', published [[December]] [[1995]] by [[Bantam Spectra]].

==Plot summary==
The fact that [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]] still lives is an annoyance to [[Bib Fortuna/Legends|Bib Fortuna]], one of the dozens of Jabba's underlings who scheme to [[Death/Legends|kill]] the [[Gangster/Legends|gangster]] and usurp his throne. To solve this problem, he is somehow involved in every plot against the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]]. As Jabba's [[Majordomo/Legends|majordomo]], Fortuna has everything set for him to take over, no matter who kills the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]]. However, because the transition of power will be rougher if another plot succeeds, Fortuna tries to keep his own plotting one step ahead of the multitude of other plots against Jabba. In order to gain this advantage, he has allied himself with the [[B'omarr Order/Legends|B'omarr Monks]]. Unknown to Fortuna, the monks have their own plan, and Jabba is not their only target.

When he learns that his old friend [[Nat Secura]] is to be executed by the Hutt, ha has the monks surgically extract Secura's [[Brain/Legends|brain]] for safekeeping in a jar. Despite his repeated promises to secure his friend a new body, Fortuna never delivers as he is distracted by business, such as meeting with [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], who wants to arrange [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo's]] return. When Luke's rescue plan results in Jabba's destruction, Fortuna escapes the [[Sail barge/Legends|sail barge]] explosion in a [[Skiff/Legends|skiff]] and returns to the [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|palace]]. He is overpowered by the B'omarr monks, who disembrain him, leaving his gray matter in a jar.

==Continuity==
[[Bib Fortuna/Legends|Fortuna's]] brain would appear again in a comic series [[Star Wars: X-Wing Rogue Squadron: Battleground: Tatooine|''X-Wing Rogue Squadron: Battleground: Tatooine'']] ([[1996]]) and eventually be returned to a fresh-and-blood [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] body. [[Nat Secura]] would appear in the ''[[Star Wars: Republic]]'' series story [[Star Wars: Rite of Passage|''Rite of Passage'']] ([[2002]]), set during his childhood. This character established the [[Clan Secura|Secura clan]] name, from which the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Aayla Secura/Legends|Aayla]] also hails.<ref name="TERC" />

